    <item>
      <title>Project Reflect</title>
      <link>https://shutowl.github.io/blog/project-reflect/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 20 Aug 2021 13:02:40 -0700</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://shutowl.github.io/blog/project-reflect/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h5 id=&#34;posted-on-august-20-2021&#34;&gt;Posted on August 20, 2021&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It took a while (mostly because of procrastination) but I&amp;rsquo;ve finally got a prototype
of a simple bullet hell game where you can reflect (almost) everything that 
I call &amp;ldquo;Project Reflect&amp;rdquo; (working title).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Originally, I planned for a bullet hell game with a gimmick, so I based the game on this reflect mechanic.
So far, it only reflects one type of bullet and pushes enemies, but I plan to add more interactions later.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s what it looks like so far:&lt;/em&gt;

    &lt;img 
	src=&#34;https://shutowl.github.io/images/ProjectReflectUpdate9.gif&#34;  
	alt=&#34;projectreflect&#34;  
	class=&#34;left&#34;  
	style=&#34;margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;&#34;  
	width=&#34;&#34; 
	height=&#34;&#34;
	/&gt;



&lt;br&gt;
I wanted gameplay to be simple so the controls are also simple:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;       WASD: Movement
 Left Click: Reflect (2 charges)
Right Click: Dash (not shown in gif)
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
When I tried deciding on a theme for the game, I somehow ended up with &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.hololive.tv/&#34;&gt;hololive&lt;/a&gt; 
(specifically &lt;a href=&#34;https://virtualyoutuber.fandom.com/wiki/Nakiri_Ayame&#34;&gt;Ayame&lt;/a&gt;) because that was what I was mostly
interested in at the time. I admit I&amp;rsquo;m too far in the rabbithole to leave. With that said, the (rough) BGM is based on the
songs Ayame have been a part of (or in other words, a Suspect and Hyakkaryouran Hanafubuki chiptune mashup):
&lt;figure class=&#34;center&#34;&gt;
&lt;audio controls preload=&#34;metadata&#34;&gt;
&lt;source src=&#34;https://shutowl.github.io/audio/projectreflectbgm.mp3&#34; type=&#34;audio/mpeg&#34;&gt;
&lt;/audio&gt;

&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There&amp;rsquo;s a lot I plan to change later in development, like replacing the health bar with &amp;ldquo;hearts&amp;rdquo;, updating
the UI/font, adding a crosshair and other stuff. It&amp;rsquo;s also kinda boring right now with just one enemy and one
bullet type, but I plan to add more enemies with different bullet patterns and maybe even lasers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Development may be even slower now that summer break is over, but I&amp;rsquo;ll still be working on it on the side.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
